                        <article class="jeg_post jeg_pl_md_5 format-standard">
                    <div class="jeg_thumb">
                        
                        <a href="https://safety4sea.com/cm-less-is-more-the-plague-of-audit-explosion-in-maritime-operations/" aria-label="Read article: Less is more: The plague of “audit explosion” in maritime operations"><div class="thumbnail-container  size-715 "><img decoding="async" width="350" height="250" src="https://safety4sea.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/02/ee94c8b0-8fa2-4f63-8843-9cadf8d9cdf4-e1772027754771-350x250.png" class=" wp-post-image" alt="" /></div></a>
                        <div class="jeg_post_category">
                            <span><a href="https://safety4sea.com/category/others/maritime-knowledge/" class="category-maritime-knowledge">Maritime Knowledge</a></span>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                    <div class="jeg_postblock_content">
                        <h3 class="jeg_post_title">
                            <a href="https://safety4sea.com/cm-less-is-more-the-plague-of-audit-explosion-in-maritime-operations/">Less is more: The plague of “audit explosion” in maritime operations</a>
                        </h3>
                        <div class="jeg_post_meta"><div class="jeg_meta_date"><a href="https://safety4sea.com/cm-less-is-more-the-plague-of-audit-explosion-in-maritime-operations/" ><i class="fa fa-clock-o"></i> February 25, 2026</a></div></div>
                    </div>
                </article><article class="jeg_post jeg_pl_md_5 format-standard">
