                    <div class="jeg_postblock_content">
                        <h3 class="jeg_post_title">
                            <a href="https://safety4sea.com/cm-do-you-know-what-a-ship-prefix-such-as-mv-or-mt-stands-for/">Do you know what a ship prefix such as MV or MT stands for?</a>
                        </h3>
                        <div class="jeg_post_meta"><div class="jeg_meta_author coauthor"><span class="meta_text by">by</span><a href="https://safety4sea.com/author/anastasiakypriotaki/">The Editorial Team</a></div><div class="jeg_meta_date"><a href="https://safety4sea.com/cm-do-you-know-what-a-ship-prefix-such-as-mv-or-mt-stands-for/"><i class="fa fa-clock-o"></i> January 28, 2026</a></div></div>
                        <div class="jeg_post_excerpt">
                            <p>We use Mr. Ms., Dr., Capt., Sir, etc., before a person’s name as a title that matches a certain identity they bear. But did you know that ships also have a prefix that tells us something about their identity?</p>
